{{Han etyl}}

A {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} of a rake-like tool or weapon (note oracle bone script form); {{w|Guo Moruo}} considers it to be the original character for {{och-l|錡|id=1|a kind of axe or chisel}}. It was already borrowed for sound to mean "I" since the oracle bone script.

Folk etymology considers it to be an ideograph of a hand {{zh-l|*手}} holding a weapon {{zh-l|*戈}} to protect oneself.

Some have suggested a contrast with {{zh-l|*爾}}, interpreting the latter as a weapon with tip pointing outward. {{rfv-etymology|zh}}

